qas.question: What are two other job titles of the Prime Minister of the  UK?

answers.text: First Lord of the Treasury and Minister for the Civil Service

qas.question: In addition to being Prime Minister, what other role did Winston Churchill serve during World War II?

plausible_answers.text: First Lord of the Treasury and Minister for the Civil Service

qas.question: What are former titles once held by the Prime Minister of the UK?
What role did Winton Churchhill serve in during World War II rather than Prime Minister?

plausible_answers.text: Minister of Communications, Foreign Affairs, Regional Cooperation, Economy and Interior

qas.question: What roles did Benjamin Netanyahu serve in prior to serving on the cabinet of Israel?

context: As well as being head of government, a prime minister may have other roles or titles—the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, for example, is also <a0_0><b2_0>First Lord of the Treasury and Minister for the Civil Service<b2_0/><a0_0/>. Prime ministers may take other ministerial posts—for example, during the Second World War, Winston Churchill was also <a1_0><b3_0>Minister of Defence<b3_0/><a1_0/> (although there was then no Ministry of Defence), and in the current cabinet of Israel, Benjamin Netanyahu also serves as <b4_0>Minister of Communications, Foreign Affairs, Regional Cooperation, Economy and Interior
